The paper deals with convolutional dictionary learning, which is a popular technique in image processing and computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a new optimization method for CDL, which involves designing majorization matrices and incorporating momentum coefficients and restarting techniques. This suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IT (Information Theory), and cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper discusses the computational complexity and memory requirements of the proposed method, which indicates that it may also be relevant to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
